oups—Tzu Chi (the Buddhist Compassion Relief Association), Buddha's Light Mountain, Dharma Drum Mountain, and the Enacting Heaven Temple—and his analysis demonstrates that the Taiwan religious renaissance embraces a democratic modernity.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBuddhism and politicszTaiwan. 0aBuddhismzTaiwanxHistoryy20th century. 4aBuddhism. 4aGeneral (see also PHILOSOPHY Buddhist). 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh1 aMadsen, Richard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025228840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094103840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520941038423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520941038/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles